Schools will be closed on Wednesday following the rise of coronavirus cases in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Schools will be closed on Wednesday following the rise of coronavirus cases in South Africa. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced as he addressed the nation on Sunday. There are currently 61 confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Africa. WATCH: Ramaphosa addresses nation on the coronavirus pandemic “Schools will be closed from Wednesday, 18 March, and will remain closed until after the Easter weekend. To compensate, the mid-year school holidays will be shortened by a week,” said Ramaphosa. Ramaphosa added that government expects an increase in coronaviruses cases. Meanwhile, a travel ban has been imposed on high-risk countries. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.